race.comment: WRITTEN FAME (7) working nicely through his grades and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Up in trip as a ($1.30 fav), when nailed late for a close second over 1300m at Ballina. Brings a good set of figures and has further upside. MY MUM'S TOYBOY (2) tough gelding who looks to have come back even stronger this time in. Started a solid favourite when a comfortable winner over 1100m at this track. Fitter now and shapes as the main danger. GALWAY HUSSLER (9) covered ground at her second run back when a fading sixth over 1200m at Kilcoy. Will relish the drop in weight and not to be overlooked at this level. SUMO FISH (5) sent to town at his third run back when he faded late to run eleventh from the wide draw in a Randwick Country Open over 1300m. Had plenty of excuses last start and assess on earlier efforts.
